## Research Collaboration

If you use SATORI in academic research, we kindly request:

### 1. Citation

Please cite SATORI in publications using the following BibTeX:

```bibtex
@software{satori2026,
  author = {Georges BESNIER},
  title = {SATORI: Economic Operating System for Autonomous Agents},
  year = {2026},
  url = {https://github.com/satori-ai/satori},
  note = {Federated Learning + Dynamic Pricing}
}
```

### 2. Collaboration

We are actively seeking research partnerships:
- Co-authorship on papers
- Joint funding proposals (ANR, EU Horizon)
- Student engagement (internships, PhD theses)
- Technology development partnerships

Contact: contact@satori-ai.xyz 

### 3. Feedback

If your research improves SATORI:
- Share findings and improvements
- Contribute back to the project
- Participate in publications
- Help validate use cases

